ExecDesc.value: Ericom AccessNow Server Stack Buffer Overflow IPv6 version.

EngDesc.value: A stack buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Ericom AccessNow Server. The vulnerability is due to improper handling of specially crafted HTTP requests for non-existent files. A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by sending a crafted HTTP request. A successful attack can result in arbitrary code execution with SYSTEM privilege, while an unsuccessful attack will lead to a denial of service condition. Tester can turn the variable $HTTPdestPort into 8080 using the script.
